    <text type="letter">
        <body>
             <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc_es.00548.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <note type="editorial" resp="#ht" place="top"><hi rend="underline">7 P.M.</hi></note>
            <opener>
           <dateline>
                <name type="place"><handShift rend="printed"/>Superintendent's Office.<ptr target="loc.07288_n1"/></name>
                <name type="place">ASYLUM FOR THE INSANE</name>
                <name type="place">LONDON. ONTARIO</name>
                <name type="place">London, Ont.,</name>
                <date when="1888-12-25"><handShift rend="manuscript"/>25 Dec <handShift rend="printed"/>188<handShift rend="manuscript"/>8</date> 
            </dateline>   
             </opener> 
                <p>Your card of 23d to hand by this morning mail<ptr target="loc.07288_n2"/>—glad to hear that you are holding
                your grip—We have had a quiet Xmas—we have eaten 122 turkeys—80
                geese and over 400 lbs of plum pudding—regular English style! For my own part
                I have just had a glorious dinner of roast turkey and plum pudding and feel well! My
                great anxiety now is to put meter matters<ptr target="loc.07230_n2"/> in such shape that I may get to Phila and
                see yourself and Traubel<ptr target="n4267"/> and see with my own eyes how things are <pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="loc_es.00549.jpg" type="verso"/>
                with you.</p>
               <p>Must close this letter and go upstairs to the amusement room where we have Xmas trees
                for the patients and then dancing</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>Love and good luck to you</salute>
                <signed>RM Bucke</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_es.00546.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc_es.00547.jpg" type="verso"/>
        </body>
    </text>
